# Java Break: Control Flow and Conditionals

Welcome back to another exciting episode of Java Break! In this segment, we'll cover the topics of *Control Flow* and *Conditionals*.

You first encounter one type of Control Flow in the first course - the `if/else` statement.
```java
if (condition)
     // Code to be executed
else
     // Code to be executed
```

Later, [Chris showed you](https://classroom.udacity.com/nanodegrees/nd803/parts/54293ab0-253b-410d-be3d-6662cc3fd071/modules/ef9aab21-f124-4354-9aee-581db628214e/lessons/1335cf7d-bb4f-48c6-8503-f14b127d2abc/concepts/feb082f7-3824-4a31-8d7b-cd1f70d94588?contentVersion=3.0.0&contentLocale=en-us) how to use the `switch statement` to display the correct color value based on the current earthquake's magnitude.

```java
switch (magnitudeFloor) {
        case 0:
        case 1:
            magnitudeColorResourceId = R.color.magnitude1;
            break;
        case 2:
            magnitudeColorResourceId = R.color.magnitude2;
            break;
...
```

